{
  "doc_id": "39966",
  "text": "Available evidence about the effect of adiposity on circulating irisin has been controversial. Liu and co-workers found a positive association of irisin with BMI and glucose in non-diabetic subjects but not in diabetes patients, even after adjustment for multiple covariates [CITATION_1] . The positive association of circulating irisin with BMI has also been found in two other non-diabetic populations [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Huh and co-workers further found that muscle mass was the main predictor for circulating irisin [CITATION_4] . In contrast to these reports above, Moreno-Navarrete et al. found a negative association of circulating irisin with BMI, waist-hip ratio and fat mass in men; although they did find FNDC5 expression in human muscle positively correlated with BMI as well as PGC-1a expression [CITATION_5] . Therefore, further studies are warranted to address this discrepancy on the effect of adiposity on circulating irisin.",
